where t-norm T {·} is a generalization of the usual two-valued logical conjunction (studied in classical logic), w1 and w2 ∈ [0, 1] mean weights of importance of the arguments a1, a2 ∈ [0, 1]. Please note that T ∗ {a1, a2; 1, 1} = T {a1, a2} and T ∗ {a1, a2; 1, 0} = a1.
- cthi ∈ [0, 1] - coefficient determined experimentally for each user to eliminate disproportion between FAR and FRR error (see e.g. [48]). The values of this coefficient are usually close to 0.5.
